# Android-Specific Development Rules
# Last Updated: 2024-04-10

## Android Development Guidelines

### Google Play Billing
- Use Google Play Billing Library
- Implement proper purchase verification
- Handle subscription lifecycle
- Test with Google Play billing sandbox
- Support subscription upgrades/downgrades

### Android-Specific Features
- Handle Android lifecycle properly
- Support different Android versions
- Implement proper permissions
- Handle configuration changes
- Support Android-specific gestures

### Material Design
- Follow Material Design 3 guidelines
- Implement proper theming
- Support dynamic colors
- Handle different screen densities
- Support RTL layouts

### Performance
- Optimize app size
- Implement proper ProGuard rules
- Handle background processes
- Optimize battery usage
- Implement proper caching

### Testing
- Use JUnit for unit tests
- Implement Espresso UI tests
- Test different Android versions
- Test on various devices
- Test different screen sizes

### Google Play Store
- Follow Play Store guidelines
- Prepare store listing
- Handle app signing
- Implement proper crash reporting
- Keep privacy policy up-to-date

### Security
- Implement proper encryption
- Handle sensitive data securely
- Use proper authentication
- Follow Android security best practices
- Implement proper data backup
 